Executive Profile
Cyrus F. Freidheim Jr.Chief Executive Officer of Sun-Times Media Group and President of Sun-Times Media Group, CNLC-STC, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships82--
Background

		Mr. Cyrus F. Freidheim, Jr. served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Sun-Times Media Group Inc., a parent company of Sun-Times News Group (formerly, Hollinger International Inc.) from November 14, 2006 to February 28, 2009. Mr. Freidheim served as a Publisher of the Chicago Sun-Times of Sun-Times Media Group Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Chiquita Brands International Inc., from March 19, 2002 to January 2004 and its President since May ... 2002. Mr. Freidheim has over 40 years of business experience. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Sun-Times Media, LLC (also known as Chicago Sun-Times, Inc) until February 2009. Mr. Freidheim was with Booz Allen & Hamilton Inc. for 35 years. He joined Booz Allen & Hamilton in 1966 and served as Managing Director of several international offices, including the US Office. He served as the President of BoozAllen International. Mr. Freidheim began his nearly 50-year career as a Plant Engineer at Union Carbide Corporation, after serving in the Security Group of the US Navy. He was also employed at Ford Motor Company's central finance staff. He has been the Chairman of Old Harbour Partners since 2004. Mr. Freidheim serves as Chair of Thunderbird American Graduate School of Institutional Management. He served as the Chairman of Chiquita Brands International Inc., from March 19, 2002 to May 25, 2004. From 1990 to March 2002, Mr. Freidheim served as Vice Chairman of Booz Allen & Hamilton Inc., which he served in various other leadership capacities from 1966 to March 2002 and as Vice Chairman, he led it through a period a dramatic growth. He serves as Lead Director of HSBC Financial Corp. Ltd., and has been its Director since September 1992. He has been Director of Security Capital Group Inc., since 1991. He serves as a Director of CS Tech Inc. and Pharmaceutical Industries LLC. He serves as a Life Trustee of Rush University, Rush University Medical Center and The Brookings Institution. He serves as a Trustee of the institutional boards including the American China Forum, Chicago Council on Foreign Relations (of which he is Former Chairman), the Commercial Club of Chicago, Chicago Symphony Orchestra, Garvin School of International Management (of which he is Former Chairman) and Big Shoulders Fund for Parochial Schools. He served as Director of MicroAge, Inc. since January 29, 1998 and Allegheny Energy Supply Company, LLC since 2003. He served as Non-Employee Director of Virgin America Inc. from 2006 to December 14, 2016. He served as a Director of SITEL Corporation since October 2005 and Chiquita Brands International Inc., from March 2002 to May 25, 2004. Mr. Freidheim served as Independent Director of Allegheny Energy Inc. from October 13, 2003 to February 25, 2011 and served as its Presiding Director from May 20, 2010 to February 25, 2011. Mr. Freidheim served as Lead Director and Director of HSBC Finance Corp. (formerly, Household International Inc.) since 1992. He served as an Independent Director of Sun-Times Media Group Inc., from 2006 to January 16, 2009. Mr. Freidheim is a Member of the Advisory Council of the Mendosa School of Business at the University of Notre Dame. Mr. Freidheim holds a BS in Chemical Engineering from the University of Notre Dame, an MS in Industrial Administration from Carnegie Mellon University, a Ph.D (Honorary) in International Law from Thunderbird, The Garvin School of International Management and an MBA from Carnegie Mellon University.Read Full Background




